    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For an aging lab, a protein-to-fat ratio that is well-balanced but focuses on quality ingredients is key. You'll want to look for foods that are high in quality, digestible protein, but also contain healthy fats, especially Omega-3s, to support joint health. Generally, aim for a food that is at least 30-35% protein on a dry matter basis, with fats around 15-25%. Always check the specific life-stage guidelines for senior dogs in the food's nutrition label.",
